ENTRY            F0528   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0528001   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  8         16
TITLE      Structure of low-lying states of 56,58Fe nuclei by
           alpha-particle inelastic scattering
AUTHOR     (F.Ballester,E.Casal,J.B.A.England)
INSTITUTE  (2SPNVAL,2UK BIR)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,501,301,1989)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2UK BIR) A.V.F. Radial Ridge cyclotron.
ANALYSIS    The differential cross sections were normalized to the
           prediction of the optical potential model for elastic
           scattering at the angle < 50 degr. where Coulomb
           scattering is dominant.
ERR-ANALYS The energy resolution was about 150 keV FWHM for 2(1)+,
           3- and 4(1)+ states and 250 keV for the other excited
           states.
HISTORY    (20030627C)
           (20251214U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           ANG-ERR -> ANG-ERR-D; DATA-ERR -> ERR-DIG.
ENDBIB              16
COMMON               3          3
EN         ANG-ERR-D  ERR-DIG
MEV        ADEG       PER-CENT
  25.0       0.5         0.2
ENDCOMMON            3
